  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Organisational Development of Theatre for a Change UK</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">TFAC is a small organisation with a track record of attracting donor funds: Comic Relief currently funds a TFAC Malawi project, which promotes female sex workers&apos; access to legal and health services. This application builds on a number of recommendations outlined in a recently completed external review, including: developing more transparent and effective communication between different sections of the organisation; raising the external profile of the organisation, its &#xE2;&#x20AC;&#x2DC;value added&apos; and cost effectiveness; documenting the organisation&apos;s approaches; consolidating and refining tools and materials; and strengthening overall M&amp;E quality at different levels. These have become a central part of TFAC&apos;s Organisational Strategy 2012-2015. To address these issues this grant will support a workshop for all UK Trustees on the TFAC methodology; four UK trustees will travel to Ghana and Malawi to increase their understanding of the work and establish a partnership scheme; the TFAC training modules will be documented and accredited; and an operations manual developed. An external consultant will undertake an M&amp;E review and develop a framework with common outcomes and indicators for all partners. A value for money (VfM) assessment will be conducted to ensure programmes are cost effective and that staff consider VfM in programme development. Finally, an external review of external and internal communications systems will be undertaken and staff will be supported to implement recommendations. A number of the organisational development activities outlined in the proposal rely on the intervention of an external consultant. Therefore it is important that the organisation finds ways to ensure the learning from this grant is institutionalised, including by sharing learning with its Federation partners.</narrative>
  </description>
